content.body: Note that SpiderMonkey lazily initializes properties on functions, so you will get a different result if you access a property before enumerating them (eg `function foo() {}; foo.name; Object.keys(...` will give `["name", "prototype", "length"]`)

content.body: sounds like we have potentially 3 different behaviors then, and we should make some test262 tests
